obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (18945)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Dissolution of Rehabilitation Council and transfer of rights, liabilities and employees of Rehabilitation Council to Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00015_199234_1517807323807&sectionId=18945&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00015_199234_1517807323807
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the date of the constitution of the Council, the`
  line `Rehabilitation Council shall stand dissolved and on such dissolution,--`
  line
  line `(a) all properties and assets, movable and immovable, of, or belonging to, the Rehabilitation`
  line `Council shall vest in the Council;`
  line
  line `(b) all the rights and liabilities of the Rehabilitation Council shall be transferred to, and be the`
  line `rights and liabilities of, the Council;`
  line
  line `(c) without prejudice to the provisions of clause (b), all liabilities incurred, all contracts entered`
  line `into and all matters and things engaged to be done by, with or for the Rehabilitation Council`
  line `immediately before that date, for or in connection with the purposes of the said Rehabilitation`
  line `Council shall be deemed to have been incurred, entered into, or engaged to be done by, with or for,`
  line `the Council;`
  line
  line `(d) all sums of money due to the Rehabilitation Council immediately before that date shall be`
  line `deemed to be due to the Council;`
  line
  line `(e) all suits and other legal proceedings instituted or which could have been instituted by or`
  line `against the Rehabilitation Council immediately before that date may be continued or may be`
  line `instituted by or against the Council; and`
  line
  line `(f) every employee holding any office under the Rehabilitation Council immediately before that`
  line `date shall hold his office in the Council by the same tenure and upon the same terms and conditions of`
  line `service as respects remuneration, leave, provident fund, retirement and other terminal benefits as he`
  line `would have held such office as if the Council had not been constituted and shall continue to do so as`
  line `an employee of the Council or until the expiry of a period of six months from that date if such`
  line `employee opts not to be the employee of the Council within such period.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947) or any other`
  line `law for the time being in force, absorption of any employee by the Council in its regular service under this`
  line `section shall not entitle such employee to any compensation under that Act or other law and no such claim`
  line `shall be entertained by any court, tribunal or other authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, "Rehabilitation Council" means the Rehabilitation Council, a society`
  line `formed and registered under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860) and functioning as such`
  line `immediately before the constitution of the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (18946)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Recognition of qualifications granted by University, etc., in India for rehabilitation professionals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00015_199234_1517807323807&sectionId=18946&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00015_199234_1517807323807
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The qualifications granted by any University or other institution in India which are`
  line `included in the Schedule shall be recognised qualifications for rehabilitation professionals.`
  line
  line `(2) Any University or other institution which grants qualification for the rehabilitation professionals`
  line `not included in the Schedule may apply to the Central Government to have any such qualification`
  line `recognised, and the Central Government, after consulting the Council may, by notification, amend the`
  line `Schedule so as to include such qualification therein and any such notification may also direct that an entry`
  line `shall be made in the last column of the Schedule against such qualification only when granted after a`
  line `specified date.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
