obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (18956)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Professional conduct and removal of names from Register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00015_199234_1517807323807&sectionId=18956&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00015_199234_1517807323807
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may prescribe`
  line `standards of professional conduct and etiquette and a code of ethics for rehabilitation professionals.`
  line
  line `(2) Regulations made by the Council under sub-section (1) may specify which violations thereof shall`
  line `constitute infamous conduct in any professional respect, that is to say, professional misconduct, and such`
  line `provision shall have effect notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in`
  line force.
  line
  line `(3) The Council may order that the name of any person shall be removed from the Register where it is`
  line `satisfied, after giving that person a reasonable opportunity of being heard, and after such further inquiry,`
  line `if any, as it may deem fit to make,--`
  line
  line `(i) that his name has been entered in the Register by error or on account of misrepresentation or`
  line `suppression of a material fact;`
  line
  line `(ii) that he has been convicted of any offence or has been guilty of any infamous conduct in any`
  line `professional respect, or has violated the standards of professional conduct and etiquette or the code of`
  line `ethics prescribed under sub-section (1) which, in the opinion of the Council, renders him unfit to be`
  line `kept in the Register.`
  line
  line `(4) An order under sub-section (3) may direct that any person whose name is ordered to be removed`
  line `from the Register shall be ineligible for registration under this Act either permanently or for such period`
  line `of years as may be specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (18957)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Appeal against order of removal from Register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 2000, s. 7, for "period of thirty days" (w.e.f. 4-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00015_199234_1517807323807&sectionId=18957&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00015_199234_1517807323807
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the name of any person has been`
  line `removed from the Register on any ground other than that he is not possessed of the requisite rehabilitation`
  line `qualifications, he may appeal, in the prescribed manner and subject to such conditions, including`
  line `conditions as to the payment of a fee, as may be prescribed to the Central Government whose decision`
  line `thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(2) No appeal under sub-section (1) shall be admitted if it is preferred after the expiry of a ^1[period of`
  line `sixty days] from the date of the order under sub-section (3) of section 21:`
  line
  line `Provided that an appeal may be admitted after the expiry of the said ^1[period of sixty days] if the`
  line `appellant satisfies the Central Government that he had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within`
  line `the said period.`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (18958)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title Register.
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00015_199234_1517807323807&sectionId=18958&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00015_199234_1517807323807
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the Member-Secretary to keep and maintain the Register in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act and any order made by the Council and from time to time to`
  line `revise the Register and publish it in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(2) The Register shall be deemed to be a public document within the meaning of the Indian Evidence`
  line `Act, 1872 (1 of 1872) and may be proved by a copy thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (18959)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Information to be furnished by Council and publication thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00015_199234_1517807323807&sectionId=18959&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00015_199234_1517807323807
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall`
  line `furnish such reports, copies of its minutes, abstracts of its accounts, and other information to the Central`
  line `Government as that Government may require.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may publish in such manner as it may think fit, any report, copy, abstract`
  line `or other information furnished to it by the Council under this section or under section 16.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (18960)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00015_199234_1517807323807&sectionId=18960&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00015_199234_1517807323807
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), no court shall take cognizance of an offence punishable under this Act`
  line `except upon a complaint, in writing, made by any person authorised in this behalf by the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (18961)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00015_199234_1517807323807&sectionId=18961&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00015_199234_1517807323807
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government, Council, Chairperson, members, Member-Secretary or any officer or`
  line `other employee of the Council for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (18962)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Employees of Council to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00015_199234_1517807323807&sectionId=18962&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00015_199234_1517807323807
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson, members, Member-Secretary,`
  line `officers and other employees of the Council shall, while acting or purporting to act in pursuance of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or of any rule and regulation made thereunder, be deemed to be public servants`
  line `within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (18963)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00015_199234_1517807323807&sectionId=18963&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00015_199234_1517807323807
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification, make rules to carry out`
  line `the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (18964)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00015_199234_1517807323807&sectionId=18964&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00015_199234_1517807323807
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The Council may, with the previous sanction of the Central`
  line `Government, make, by notification, regulations generally to carry out the purposes of this Act, and`
  line `without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the management of the property of the Council;`
  line
  line `(b) the maintenance and audit of the accounts of the Council;`
  line
  line `(c) the resignation of members of the Council;`
  line
  line `(d) the powers and duties of the Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(e) the rules of procedure in the transaction of business under sub-section (3) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(f) the function of the Executive Committee and other committees, constituted under section 7;`
  line
  line `(g) the powers and duties of the Member-Secretary under sub-section (1) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(h) the qualifications, appointment, powers and duties of, and procedure to be followed by,`
  line `Inspectors and Visitors;`
  line
  line `(i) the courses and period of study or of training, to be undertaken, the subjects of examination`
  line `and standards of proficiency therein to be obtained in any University or any institution for grant of`
  line `recognised rehabilitation qualification;`
  line
  line `(j) the standards of staff, equipment, accommodation, training and other facilities for study or`
  line `training of the rehabilitation professionals;`
  line
  line `(k) the conduct of examinations, qualifications of examiners, and the condition of the admission`
  line `to such examinations;`
  line
  line `(l) the standards of professional conduct and etiquette and code of ethics to be observed by`
  line `rehabilitation professionals under sub-section (1) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(m) the particulars to be stated, and proof of qualifications to be given, in application for`
  line `registration under this Act;`
  line
  line `(n) the manner in which and the conditions subject to which an appeal may be preferred under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 22;`
  line
  line `(o) the fees to be paid on applications and appeals under this Act;`
  line
  line `(p) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (18965)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Laying of rules and regulations before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00015_199234_1517807323807&sectionId=18965&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00015_199234_1517807323807
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and every regulation made`
  line `under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it`
  line `is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation, or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
